Class RomanisableString

Namespace
osu.Framework.Localisation
Assembly
osu.Framework.dll

A string that has a romanised fallback to allow a better experience for users that potentially can't read the original script. See ShowUnicode, which can toggle the display of romanised variants.

public class RomanisableString : IEquatable<RomanisableString>, ILocalisableStringData, IEquatable<ILocalisableStringData>

Constructors

RomanisableString(string?, string?)

Construct a new romanisable string.

public RomanisableString(string? original, string? romanised)

Parameters

original string

The string in its original script. If null, the romanised version will always be used.

romanised string

The romanised version of the string. If null, the original version will always be used.

Remarks

For flexibility, both of the provided strings are allowed to be null. If both are null, the returned string value from GetLocalised(LocalisationParameters) will be Empty.
